2.title: Keep the Peace
2.plot: This second webisode begins with Turturro adding a fresh installment to his video diary for his mom. We then head out to the beach, where he and Paige are coming in from a morning of surfing, and she helps him work through what he sees as a problem with his investigation of the Malaysian gang. Later, she reluctantly makes a call for him that opens up a new investigative path.

3.title: Ain't Got That Swing
3.plot: Webisode 3 begins again with Turturro making a fresh installment to his video diary for his mom. These pick up the story line and lay out where he is in the investigation of the Malaysian counterfeit gang. We then find him getting a golf lesson from Mike Warren, who is a helluva good golfer, so he can be more successful when he goes undercover to "play" Hani, the gang's leader.

4.title: Forbidden Fruit
4.plot: Webisode 4 begins again with Turturro making a fresh installment to his video diary for his mom. These pick up the story line and lay out where he is in the investigation of the Malaysian counterfeit gang (it's funny when he talks about how the golf game went). He then turns to BRIGGS for help deciphering an encrypted message that appears in the form of a coded text, which leads him to a night time stakeout.

5.title: Goose Chase
5.plot: Webisode 5 begins again with Turturro in his room, making a fresh installment to his video diary for his mom. These pick up the serialized story line and lay out where he is in the investigation of the Malaysian counterfeit gang. Then he teams up with Charlie and they go undercover to meet Hani at a restaurant, where they have to deftly get him to incriminate himself on their hidden recorder.

6.title: Action
6.plot: This is the final webisode in this series, and of course it is where it all comes together - in a pretty surprising way. The crew discovers Manny's video diary, and they aren't happy about it at all. But after he explains, they forgive him and actually help out with a special message for his mom. And not spoiling it, but there is a reason this webisode is called , "ACTION."

-1.title: Fakes for Jakes
-1.plot: In this opening webisode, Johnny establishes that he is creating a video diary on his computer for his mom to watch someday. He reveals that he is gonna go after a local Malaysian gang of counterfeiters. He then seeks the help and guidance of his friend Jakes with some tech and in exchange, offers to help him move some boxes.

imdb.title: Graceland Insider
synopsis: Johnny Turturro gets his own case. He has to infiltrate and bust a cabal of cellphone conterfeiters that happens to be run by a ruthless Malaysian-American crime figure (fictional of course). In each episode, he enlists the help of a different Graceland roommate to get the job done. This series is a great way to learn more about and get more personally connected to Johnny as a continuing character on the show (played with charming brilliance by the very talented Manny Montana). The final ep. has a really fun "home-made movie" that is definitely not the usual thing you'd see in the series, but fits the playful side of the characters' personalities. Each of the original 3-4 minute mini-episodes were produced in May of 2014 and rolled out on USANetwork.com one at a time after each new Graceland Season Two episode appeared live on TV. They are sponsored by Toyota.
